[[File:COLLECTIE TROPENMUSEUM Portret van de leerlingen van de Algemene Middelbare School afdeling B te Yogyakarta ter gelegenheid van het vertrek van G.A.J. Hazeu terug naar Nederland 1920 TMnr 60025982.jpg|thumb|Portrait of the AMS students Section B [[Yogyakarta]] to mark the departure of G.A.J. Hazeu back to the Netherlands in 1920]]
'''Algemene Middelbare School''' or '''AMS''' ([[Dutch language|Dutch]], "General Secondary School") was during part of the twentieth century a level of education in the Netherlands (and the [[Dutch East Indies]]<ref>{{cite book |title=Upuleru |last=Siwabessy |first=G.A. |authorlink=G.A. Siwabessy |year=1979 |publisher=PT Gunung Agung |location=[[Jakarta]] |isbn= |language=Indonesian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://pakguruonline.pendidikan.net/sjh_pdd_sumbar_bab3a.html |title=Pendidikan Pemerintah Hindia Belanda |author= |year=2010 |work= |publisher=PakGuru Online |accessdate=19 August 2012}}</ref>), comparable with the [[Secondary school| high school]] level in the US education system. Its successors were the mavo and vbo, now both replaced by [[Voorbereidend middelbaar beroepsonderwijs|vmbo]].
