'''Lord Morpheous''' is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] sex educator, author and photographer based in New York. He is the author of ''How to Be Kinky: A Beginner’s Guide to BDSM'', ''How to Be Kinkier: More Adventures in Adult Playtime'' and ''Bondage Basics: Naughty Knots and Risque Restraints You Need to Know''.<ref name="Sexual Representation Collection">{{cite web |url=http://www.uc.utoronto.ca/sexual-representation-collection|title=Sexual Representation Collection|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=University of Toronto|publisher=University of Toronto|accessdate=11 November 2013}}</ref> Morpheous' work is archived in the Sexual Representation Collection of the [[University of Toronto]]'s Mark S. Bonham Centre for Sexual Diversity Studies,<ref name="Sexual Representation Collection" /> at the [[Leather Archives and Museum]] in [[Chicago]], and at the [[National Archives of Canada]].<ref name="HTBK pg 310">{{cite book|last=Morpheous|title=How to Be Kinkier: More Adventures in Adult Playtime|year=2012|publisher=Green Candy Press|isbn=978-1931160940|page=310}}</ref> Morpheous has taught a variety of workshops on [[rope bondage]], the aesthetics of bondage, [[fetish photography]], advanced and beginner [[BDSM]], and workshops catered to professional dominants and submissives.<ref name="How to be Kinky">{{cite book|last=Morpheous|title=How to be Kinky: A Beginner's Guide to BDSM|year=2008|publisher=Green Candy Press|isbn=978-1931160636|page=Back Cover}}</ref> He is also the founder of Morpheous’ Bondage Extravaganza, an annual rope bondage themed art installation.<ref name="MBE website">{{cite web |url=http://mbe2013.com/about-mbe/|title=About MBE|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=Morpheous’ Bondage Extravaganza |accessdate=11 November 2013}}</ref>

==Education==
Morpheous gained a B.Ed and an Honours BA in Visual Art with a Minor in English. He also has a Degree in Broadcasting.

==Morpheous' Bondage Extravaganza==
Lord Morpheous hosts an annual event called Morpheous' Bondage Extravaganza (also known as MBE), an annual public display of rope bondage during the [[Nuit Blanche]] festival in Toronto.<ref name="HTBK pg 310" /> The event features 12 hours of rope bondage art ranging from simple bondage performed on the floor to aerial suspension.<ref name="MBE website" /> This installation is not an official part of Nuit Blanche. According to the event website, the first Morpheous’ Bondage Extravaganza took place in a storefront window on Toronto's [[Queen Street West]] in 2007, and has since grown to a 4,000 square foot venue in Toronto.<ref name="MBE website" /> The event is also live-streamed over the internet and has also recently expanded to include an MBE in [[Orlando, Florida]] and [[San Francisco, California]].<ref name="MBE Orlando">{{cite web |url=http://mbe2013.com/mbe-orlando/|title=MBE Orlando|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=Morpheous' Bondage Extravaganza|accessdate=11 November 2013}}</ref> The event has grown over the years, and has attracted 6000 attendees cross the three cities with another 75,000 watching online.<ref name="MBE website" />

==KinkMe App==
Morpheous is the creator of the KinkMe app.<ref name="Kink Me website">{{cite web |url=http://kinkme.ca/main.html|title=Kink Me|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |year=2012|website=Kink Me|publisher=Morpheous Productions|accessdate=11 November 2013}}</ref> This app is designed to help the user determine their "kink compatibility" with other KinkMe app users.<ref name="Kink Me website" /> It instructs the user to fill out a checklist of kinky activities and then bump phones with another user to compare their kink interests and gauge their compatibility.<ref name="Google Kink Me App">{{cite web |url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.lordmorpheous.kinkmeandroid|title=Kink Me - Kink List Comparison|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=Google Play|publisher=Google|accessdate=11 November 2013}}</ref>

==Altsexed==
Altsexed is a website dedicated to lectures and classes by Morpheous. According to the website altsexed.com, lectures and classes by Morpheous are suitable for: 
* human sexuality courses and psychology & social studies
